snippet.textDisplay: I think there is a big difference in culture when it comes to saying "I love you." I don't know if she is from Russia per se, but typically in similar countries, the man has to win the woman's love, through taking care of her, supporting her, until one day their relationship develops to the level of love. And same vice versa. No offence to Americans, but they throw that word out very often without truly meaning it. In addition, people from Russia and similar countries are typically more honest about their intentions. You think every 30 year old woman or 40 year old man in America married because of love? Or was it time to settle down and their significant other was good enough to settle down with... For her it doesn't seem like too big of an issue to be up front (and at least she is not lying), but I get that for Americans its not what your future wife should be saying, and that its difficult for him to understand.
